1	/**
2	 * Scheduler — orchestration loop that drives the Yoke pipeline.
3	 *
4	 * The Scheduler is the glue layer that wires all existing building blocks into
5	 * a real workflow execution engine.  On start() it:
6	 *
7	 *   1. Calls ingestWorkflow() to seed workflow + item rows into SQLite.
8	 *   2. Calls buildCrashRecovery() to detect stale sessions from a previous run.
9	 *   3. Transitions stale in_progress items → session_fail so they don't get
10	 *      double-spawned.
11	 *   4. Enters a poll/event loop (default 500 ms tick).
12	 *
13	 * ## Tick loop
14	 *
15	 *   Each tick re-reads all non-terminal workflows from SQLite (RC-1: no
16	 *   in-memory cache).  For every item:
17	 *     - pending           → fire deps_satisfied (moves to ready when deps met)
18	 *     - ready             → fire phase_start → bootstrapping | in_progress
19	 *     - bootstrapping     → createWorktree + runBootstrap → bootstrap_ok | fail
20	 *     - in_progress (not  → spawn agent session (full async lifecycle)
21	 *       in inFlight)
22	 *     - awaiting_retry    → fire backoff_elapsed after RETRY_BACKOFF_MS
23	 *     - rate_limited      → fire rate_limit_window_elapsed after reset_at
24	 *
25	 * ## Concurrency
26	 *
27	 *   Max parallel sessions read from SQLite on every tick (RC-5). Items being
28	 *   managed in the inFlight map count against the limit.
29	 *
30	 * ## Guarantees
31	 *
32	 *   RC-1  Every scheduling decision re-reads SQLite — no in-memory workflow
33	 *         cache between loop ticks.
34	 *   RC-2  All SQLite mutations go through engine functions (applyItemTransition,
35	 *         applyWorktreeCreated, insertSession, updateSessionPid, endSession).
36	 *         No direct db.writer calls in this file.
37	 *   RC-3  Process spawn happens only after the in_progress transition is
38	 *         committed (applyItemTransition returns before spawn).
39	 *   RC-4  buildCrashRecovery() is called before any new items are scheduled.
40	 *   RC-5  Concurrency limit enforced by counting running sessions in SQLite
41	 *         plus items currently being processed (not yet in SQLite).
42	 *   RC-6  ProcessManager, WorktreeManager, PromptAssemblerFn, and
43	 *         PrePostRunnerFn are all injectable for integration testing.
44	 */
45	
46	import crypto from 'node:crypto';
47	import path from 'node:path';
48	import type { DbPool } from '../storage/db.js';
